=== Perl

MovieDB is expected to be run at least in Perl 5.10.

=== Database

MovieDB assumes background database is PostreSQL >= v9.0, however it may work on lower versions.

=== Packages

MovieDB depends on following CPAN packages and their default dependencies:

	* Carp
		For pretty-formatted die and warn messages.
	
	* Try::Tiny
		For exception handling.
	
	* Data::Dumper::Perltidy
		For pretty-printing dumped objects while debugging.
	
	* ToolSet
		For automating boilerplate use, pragma and version code.
	
	* DBIx::Class
		Object Relational Mapper
	
	* UUID::Tiny
		For creating UUID4 primary keys
